      "text": "After returning to Argentina in 1919, [[Enrique Telémaco Susini]] started working on the conversion of an old circus site into the [[Teatro Coliseo]] theater. Together with his friends, he started planning for a radio transmission from there, strongly supported by the two Italian owners, Faustino da Rossa and Walter Mocchi."
